,Recommended,213330,9756541,"Posted: 7 April, 2014",all,Revan1207,"LEGO Batman 2 is the sequel to LEGO Batman... which is obvious. I don't completely know why I got this since I didn't care much for the first LEGO Batman, but this one is an improvement. I'm not too far into the game, but I can tell you it is definitely not bad.The story isn't too bad. The Joker is trying to defeat Batman once again, but this time Lex Luthor is by his side along with many other villains. Like LEGO Marvel Super Heroes, this game mixes the super hero/comic book storyline with what you expect from a Lego game very well.The gameplay is pretty much what you expect from a Lego game- do missions, build stuff, get gold bricks, get characters, etc. It is fun, but there's something about the LEGO Batman games that seem a bit boring to me as far as levels go and I don't really know what it is. When you aren't doing missions, you can free roam around Gotham City, like you can free roam around New York in LEGO Marvel Super Heroes, and this is pretty fun.The graphics for LEGO Batman 2 are about the same as most Lego games. Gotham City has the kind of look that reminds you of the Batman Arkham games, which fits very well with Batman. The animations look good as well.Probably the main problems I have with this game are what I mentioned before about the levels and the amount of characters. I don't have all of them yet, but there don't seem to be very many. From what I can tell, there's probably around 50 of them. Not bad, but still much less than I expected.LEGO Batman 2 definitely isn't the best Lego game so far, but it is definitely not the worst either. It has a plot that goes good with both Batman/DC Comics and Lego, entertaining free roam, and a good amount of characters. However, if you're looking for a Lego game that you'll be playig for hours at a time, go with LEGO Marvel Super Heroes or LEGO Star Wars.I give LEGO Batman 2 an 8/10."
