,Recommended,213330,17568654,"Posted: 16 August, 2015",all,DigitMason,"As a follow-up to the first LEGO Batman title, LEGO Batman 2 has a lot going for it, including a much larger cast of characters, varied levels and a concise storyline, but I think it stands out most for the open-world of Gotham you can explore and (chronologically) the first inclusion of voice-acting to the series. In comparison to its prequel, a number of improvements made the experience much more seamless, including better controls, split-screen multiplayer no longer restricted to a small portion of the level, and puzzles that made better use of additional characters. The vehicle levels, while repetitive, were much more fun to play this time around. I did find some of the Gold Brick puzzles in the open-world somewhat frustrating, whether by poor design or requiring a specific character (and often specific suit). Overall a solid game, the one downside being I felt the new character roster wasn't appropriately integrated, only requiring Superman or Green Lantern a handful of times, and newcomers Flash and Cyborg serving almost no purpose."
