76561198031383772,Recommended,213330,35483099,Posted: 4 October,all,Revanaught,"This game is one of the earlier Lego games with voice acting.  As such it still manages to have a lot of the old lego game charm, where a large chunk of the jokes are told via movements and gestures rather than words.  A lot of the spoken jokes also run very well.  Some fall flat, but overall, the game is well written and quite funny.  It's refreshing to see a Batman game where Batman isn't portrayed as an omniciant god with a gadget for every situation possible.But what really got me wanting to play this game was Superman.  There are so few good Superman games out there, and this one does pretty well in his regard.  Again, the writing is really well done, and you really do feel like you're playing as Superman when you've been playing as Batman for the first couple hours, and then superman shows up and does everything biggers, better and faster.Unfortunately this game has some of the worst flight controls I've ever experienced, which makes playing as superman in the overworld really unpleasant.  Which is a real shame as that's what I was looking forward to the most.  But, that's really the only negative point I have for this.  This is absolutely a solid and worthy lego game."
